== Requirements Concept Analysis

This section analyzes requirement-level concepts: actors, goals, capabilities, conflicts, and requirement quality considerations. The purpose of this section is to describe what the system must support and how requirement concepts relate to the domain concepts defined in the Domain Concept Analysis.

=== Actors and goals
[cols="2,4",options="header"]
|===
|Actor |Primary goals

|Household member (living independently)
|Maintain an accurate understanding of availability with minimal effort, monitor spending and budget, receive alert / notification events for low-stock judgments and expiration, and reduce time spent planning replenishment.

|Household member (shared household)
|Maintain shared visibility of tracked inventory records, avoid duplicate purchases, coordinate replenishment responsibilities, and maintain a consistent shared understanding of availability and recent changes.
